    <who name="Felix Schwarz">fschwarz</who>
    <bug_when>2016-01-22 06:38:12 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>The python3 package (rawhide, git 1eeebcf2) has a patch &quot;00132-add-rpmbuild-hooks-to-unittest.patch&quot; which contains broken code (as far as I can see).

For example line 45 of said patch references a &quot;_ExpectedFailure&quot; exception which was part of unittest.case in Python 2 but isn&apos;t anymore in Python 3.

I guess that is not a problem right now (as nobody seems to have noticed the problem so far) but you probably want to review/clean up that patch.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
